Currently, not all blocks are supported for publishing, such as sets, collections, and relations.

onboardingMainGraph11: Space is essentially a graph, and Anytype aims to provide a natural way of thinking where everything is represented as objects with specific relationships, just like in the real world.
onboardingStoreType11: This Library contains all types of Objects and Properties. It comes with preinstalled types, as well as types that can be uploaded to Anytype for different use cases.
onboardingStoreType21: You can create your own types with any object layout for your own purposes. Additionally, you can save any existing object as a Library template if you need to use it frequently.
onboardingStoreType22: Now, let’s take a look at the Properties menu.
onboardingStoreRelation11: Properties are reusable links with meaning. Here you can see some examples of Properties, but the idea is that you can create your own Relations which are valuable to you and connect the Objects through them.
onboardingStoreRelation21: Establishing relations helps you to understand the graph and its structure better. You can also create Collections or Sets based on the relationships for quick access.
onboardingObjectCreationStart21: Choose here from the most popular object types, such as Page, Task, or Collection. You can also select an object from the Type menu.
emailCollectionStep0Description: Enter your email to receive tips and updates. We do not link your account with your email, ever. Cancel anytime.
emailCollectionStep1Description: Enter the code we’ve sent you to your email
emailCollectionStep2News: You are now set to receive the latest updates. Enjoy exploring!
emailCollectionStep2Tips: You are now set to receive new insights. Enjoy exploring!
emailCollectionStep2NewsAndTips: You are now set to receive the latest updates and perks. Enjoy exploring!
emailCollectionCheckboxTipsLabel: Insider tips & tutorials on using Anytype
onboardingObjectCreationFinish11: For the Object you created, you can adjust it using the top menu. Change the cover, layout, or set up a relations to build the graph.
onboardingTypeDeleted1Description: If you want to keep using this Object, change this Object Type.
onboardingSourceDeleted1Title: Please check your Installed Types & Properties
onboardingSourceDeleted1Description: Some Objects in this Set use Types or Properties that have been removed from your Space. Visit the Library to re-install these entities and continue using your Set.
onboardingInlineSet1Description: Congratulations! You can embed a Set or Collection and modify it using Filters and Views without altering the original instance.
onboardingInlineSet2Description: Adjust rules and views to suit the current context.
onboardingInlineCollection1Description: Congratulations! You can embed a set or collection and modify it using filters and views without altering the original instance.
onboardingInlineCollection2Description: Adjust rules and views to suit the current context.
onboardingDefaultTypeDescription: You can change type and template of a new object in this menu.
onboardingTemplateSelectDescription: Easily switch your templates when creating objects.
onboardingSpacesText: This is your Space. Click here to share it with others, customize its name and icon, or securely migrate from other apps.
onboardingAllObjectText: Everything in Anytype is an Object. All objects is where all your content lives.
onboardingWidgetsText: Use Widgets to create custom views of your data. Add and adjust them to suit your workflow.
onboardingMultipleSpacesText: Use the sidebar to create more spaces. Spaces allow you to collaborate seamlessly. They also help you focus on specific projects, teams or areas of your life.
onboardingGalleryText: Find use cases that match your needs. Import them from the Gallery created by the Anytype Team and Community.
onboardingMembershipText: Join the Anytype Network through a membership plan. Explore our paid features or simply support our work. We're here because of you.
onboardingSyncStatusText: View your network and peer-to-peer connection status here, along with a list of synced objects.
onboardingMobileText: Sync to your mobile devices locally. Scan the QR code to download the iOS or Android App and make use of peer-to-peer sync.
onboardingSetsText: A set gathers all objects of a certain type in your space. Explore what's already here or add more by clicking +New Object.
onboardingCollectionsText: Create an object in the collection. Use collections to store and organise handpicked objects and files.
onboardingCollaborationText: Check out the new Collaboration category to explore experiences that help you co-create, share and collaborate.
libActionUninstallTypeTitle: Do you want to remove Type "%s"?
libActionUninstallTypeText: This Type will be removed. If you have created any Objects with this Type, they may become more difficult to locate.
libActionUninstallRelationTitle: Do you want to remove Property "%s"?
libActionUninstallRelationText: This Property will be removed from your Library. If you have created any Objects with which use this Property, you will no longer be able to edit the Property value.
